                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1426">15th century, middle</origDate>. Exact origin and early provanance unknown, but the breviary was intended for a church within the diocece of <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100089">Uppsala</placeName>
                                </origPlace> (<bibl>
                                    <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107114">Helander</title>
                                    <citedRange from="191" to="191" unit="page"/>
                                    <citedRange from="408" to="408" unit="footnote"/>
                                </bibl>). According to Moberg, the manuscript belongs to a group of breviaries which also includes A 50 and A 100 of the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName>, and C 507 and W 63 of <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100002">Uppsala University Library</orgName> (<bibl>
                                    <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101394">Moberg</title>
                                    <citedRange from="1" to="1" unit="volume"/>
                                    <citedRange from="93" to="93" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>).</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Previously no. 122 in the collection of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100536">Nils Reinhold Brocman</persName>, book collector and librarian at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">Royal Library</orgName> and <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>. Upon his death in <date when="1770"/>, a large part of his book collection was donated to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>. Brocman's hand is found on <locus from="138r" to="138r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="154v" to="154v" scheme="folios"/>, and (presumably) <locus from="252v" to="252v" scheme="folios"/> (partly trimmed), comparing the contents of the breviary to the <bibl>
                                    <title type="uniform" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107368">printed edition of 1496</title>
                                </bibl>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Transferred to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> from the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
