                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1ra" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <rubric>Dominica prima aduentus domini <gap quantity="40" reason="editorial"/> cum ceteris capitulum</rubric>
                                <incipit>Fratres Scientes quia hora est</incipit>
                                <explicit>hic vere propheta qui venturus est in mundum (John 6:14) psalmus magnificat et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The Proper of time begins with the First Sunday of Advent and ends with the Twenty-fifth Sunday after Trinity. After this, the collect for the Twenty-sixth Sunday after Trinity, along with an instruction for the 22-27 Sundays after Trinity, is added by a different medieval hand (<locus from="138rb" to="138v" scheme="folios"/>). In the lower margin of <locus from="138r" to="138r" scheme="folios"/>, <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100536">Brocman</persName> has made a note comparing the addition to the contents of the <bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107368">printed edition of 1496</title>
                                        </bibl>: <quote>NB In impresso non extat Dominica XXVI sed eius loco <gap quantity="20" unit="chars" reason="damage"/>
                                        </quote>.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="139ra" to="256vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints</title>
                                <rubric>In vigilia sancti andree</rubric>
                                <incipit>In illo tempore Stabat iohannes et ex discipulis eius duo (John 1:35)</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">me praecipis munia tua devotus</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of saints begins with the vigil of St Andrew (29 Nov.). After the feast of St Catherine (25 Nov.) follow the feasts of St Clement (23 Nov.), St Theodore (9 Nov.), and St Martin (10 Nov.).</p>
                                    <p> In the process of rebinding, the bifolium making up <locus from="164" to="164" scheme="folios"/>/<locus from="174" to="174" scheme="folios"/> has been misplaced; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="163" to="163" scheme="folios"/>/<locus from="175" to="175" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="166" to="166" scheme="folios"/> consists of a small paper note which has been inserted into the manuscript. The recto transmits an excerpt from the life of St Ignatius. <!--from 
Jean de Mailly's Abbreviatio in gestis et miraculis sanctorum - likt men olikt.-->
                                    </p>
                                    <p> Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="146ra" to="146ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Anne (9 Dec.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="154rb" to="154rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Henrik (19 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="160va" to="160va" scheme="folios"/>: translation of St Erik (24 Jan.); <!--Ansgar saknas; cf. Helander s. 221-->
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="171rb" to="171rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Sigfrid (15 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="186va" to="186va" scheme="folios"/>: St Erik (18 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="188va" to="188va" scheme="folios"/>: St Eskil (12 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="190vb" to="190vb" scheme="folios"/>; St Botulf (17 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="207ra" to="207ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Olav (29 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="207rb" to="207rb" scheme="folios"/>; St Botvid (28 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="209ra" to="209ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Elin (30 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="214v" to="214v" scheme="folios"/>: St Laurence (10 Aug.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="241vb" to="241vb" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (7 Oct.).</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
